//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_depot_levy}

NOTE: This operation creates an
{rbtgi_depot}
- a cohesive unit of Recipe Bottle infrastructure including the depot project, build bucket, container repository, Mason service account, and private worker pool
that share their productive lifecycle.

The
{rbtr_payor}
creates a new depot infrastructure from the
{rbtgi_payor_project}.
The operation accepts no CLI parameters; depot identity is read from the kindled regime as `(RBRD_CLOUD_PREFIX, RBRD_DEPOT_MONIKER)`.

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_payor}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_payor_authenticate}

//axhos_step
. *Validate region against Artifact Registry locations*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations/list[locations.list] for the authenticated project
.. {rbbc_require}

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_access_oauth_probe}

NOTE: This operation probes
{rbtr_payor}
OAuth access by refreshing the stored OAuth token and then calling the Cloud Resource Manager projects.get API on the payor project.
It may repeat for a configured number of iterations with a configurable delay, enabling sustained access verification and OAuth token lifecycle testing.

The
{rbtr_payor}
role uses an OAuth 2.0 refresh token rather than a service account key, so this probe exercises the distinct authentication path through
{rbtoe_payor_authenticate}.
A successful response confirms both that the refresh token remains valid and that the payor project is accessible via CRM.

//axhos_step
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«ITERATION_COUNT»` from `--count` flag (default: 1)

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_payor_install}

The
{at_operator}
completes OAuth credential installation by running the automated installation command with the downloaded OAuth client JSON file.
This step performs the OAuth authorization flow, securely stores credentials, and validates the Payor project is accessible.

//axhoq_precondition
* {rbhg_require}
{rbrp_billing_account_id}
is set in the current shell environment

//axhoq_precondition

